The paper discusses deep neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of winner-take-all neurons and the comparison to mammalian visual processing suggest a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). The use of graphics cards for fast training suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses achieving state-of-the-art performance on image classification benchmarks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions improving the recognition of handwritten digits, which is a common topic in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
